abstract: FIRE IN WATT-STREET-TEN HORSES SMOTHERED.--Shortly after 7 o'clock Monday evening a fire broke out in a frame stable, rear of No. 65 Watt-street, occupied by cartmen and others. abstract: The year 1857 is going out with us rather gloomily, in every way. It is dismal in the item of weather, and pleasant in no other respect. Down to and through Christmas, the weather was good.
